hadithEnglish:
Mujahid said &ldquo;I was with Ibn Abbas&rdquo;. A man came to him and said that he divorced his wife by three pronouncements. I kept silence and thought that he was going to restore het to him. He then said &ldquo;A man goes and commits a foolish act and then says &ldquo;O, Ibn Abbas! Alaah has said &ldquo;And for those who fear Allaah, He (ever) prepares a way out.&rdquo; Since you did not keep duty to Allaah I do not find a way out for you. You disobeyed your Lord and your wife was separated from you. Allaah has said &ldquo;O Prophet! When you divorce women divorce them in the beginning of their waiting period.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;This tradition has been transmitted by Humaid Al Araj and by others from Mujahid on the authority of Ibn Abbas. Shubjh narrated it from Amr bin Murrah from Said bin Jubair on the authority of Ibn Abbas. Ayyub and Ibn Jubair both narrated it from &ldquo;Ikrimah bin Khalid from Said bin Jubair on the authority of Ibn Abbas. Ibn Juraij narrated it from Abd Al Hamid bin Rafi from Ata from Ibn Abbas. Al Amash narrated it from Malik bin Al Harith on the authority of Ibn Abbas. They all said about the divorce by three pronouncements. He allowed it and said&rdquo; (Your wife) has been separated from you similar to the tradition narrated by Ismail from Ayub from Abd Allaah bin Kathir.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;Hammad bin Zaid narrated it from Ayyub from Ikrimah on the authority of Ibn Abbas. This version adds If he said &ldquo;You are divorced three times saying in one pronouncement, it constitutes a single (divorce). Ismail bin Ibrahim narrated it from Ayyub from Ikrimah. This is his (Ikrimahs) statement. He did not mention the name of Ibn Abbas. He narrated it as a statement of Ikrimah.&rdquo;

Sahl bin Saad said &ldquo;The version of Musaddad has &ldquo;I witnessed the invoking of curses by the two spouses during the life time of the Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) when I was fifteen years old. When they finished invoking curses, the Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) separated them from each other. Here ends the version of Musaddad. Others said &ldquo;He was present when the Prophet (ﷺ) separated the spouses who invoked curses on each other. The man (Sahl) said &ldquo;I shall have lied against her, Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) if I keep her.

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;Some narrators did not mention the word alaiha(against her).&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;No one supported Ibn Uyainah that he separated the spouses who invoked curses.&rdquo;

 Ibn Umar said A man invoked curses on his wife (charging her of adultery) during the time of Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) and disowned the child. The Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) therefore separated them and attributed the child to the woman. Abu Dawud said &ldquo;The words narrated by Malik alone are &ldquo;and he attributed the child to the woman.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said:
The words narrated by Malik alone are: and he attributed the child to the woman.

Ubaid Allah said &ldquo;Marwan sent someone (Qabisah) to Fatimah and asked her (about the case). She said that she was the wife of Abu Hafs. The Prophet (ﷺ) appointed Ali as governor in a certain part of Yemen. Her husband also proceeded with him. From there he sent a message to her pronouncing one divorce that had yet remained. He commanded Ayyash bin Abi Rabiah and Al Harith bin Hisham to provide maintenance to her. They said &ldquo;By Allah there is no sustenance for her except in case she is pregnant.&rdquo; She came to the Prophet(ﷺ) who said &ldquo;There is no sustenance for you except in case you are pregnant. She then asked permission to shift (from her house) and he gave her permission.&rdquo; She asked &ldquo;Where should I shift. Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ)? The Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) said to Ibn Umm Maktum . He was blind. She would undress herself and he could not see her. She lived there till her waiting period passed. The Prophet (ﷺ) married her to Usamah. Qabisah then returned to Marwan and narrated that to him. Marwan said &ldquo;We did not hear this tradition except from a woman, so we shall follow the reliable practice on which we found the people&rdquo;. When this reached Fatimah she said &ldquo;between me and you is the Book of Allah&rdquo;. Allaah the exalted said &ldquo;Divorce them for their waiting period...&rdquo; Thou knowest not it may be that Allaah will afterward bring some new thing to pass. She said &ldquo;What a new thing will emerge after triple divorce.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;A similar tradition has been narrated by Yunus on the authority of Al Zuhri. As for Al Zubaidi he narrated both traditions, the tradition of Ubaid Allah in the version of Mamar and the tradition of Abu Salamah in the version of Aqil.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;Muhammad bin Ishaq narrated on the authority of Al Zuhri that Qabisah bin Dhuwaib transmitted to him the version which was narrated by Ubaid Allah bin Abd Allaah which has Qabisah then returned to Marwan and informed him about that.&rdquo;
